Music Lovers and Folks: Inshould argue about Nin usage of Classical Mrudangam in all levels of live concerts and Jugalbandi and other western cum classical concerts. Why Tabala usage is in practice instead of Mrudangam? Tabala and Mrudangam are so unique in its own way. Also it's unique in creating rhythmic ways in its own way. So, topic of discussion is, in any western classical concerts or Jugalbandi, usage of Mrudangam is limited. Why????
An Instrument creates same sort of sound, for example Tabala and Mrudangam, why Tabala and electronic machine usage is to be encouraged instead of needed usage of Mrudangam. ??? If Tabala player creates same sort of sound, even Mrudangam creates a unique way of its sound , which is different from Tabala. Hence, why Mrudangam players are not given opportunity and why they are paid accordingly ?? If a music computers cert demands percussion of Mrudangam , it's must be used. If Tabala sound is required, it must be used. But my argument is, why Tabala is used to produce same sort of Mrudangam sound, to cheat a Mrudangam player's skill??? Music creates should not encourage this, and they must insist, Mrudangam players but be used for such sorts of concerts.
